Hash: SHA1

[slackware-security]  curl (SSA:2018-136-01)

New curl packages are available for Slackware 14.0, 14.1, 14.2, and -current to
fix security issues.


Here are the details from the Slackware 14.2 ChangeLog:
+--------------------------+
patches/packages/curl-7.60.0-i586-1_slack14.2.txz:  Upgraded.
  This release contains security fixes:
  FTP: shutdown response buffer overflow
  RTSP: bad headers buffer over-read
  For more information, see:
    https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2018-1000300
    https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2018-1000301
  (* Security fix *)
+--------------------------+


Where to find the new packages:
+-----------------------------+

Thanks to the friendly folks at the OSU Open Source Lab
(http://osuosl.org) for donating FTP and rsync hosting
to the Slackware project!  :-)

Also see the "Get Slack" section on http://slackware.com for
additional mirror sites near you.

Updated package for Slackware 14.0:
ftp://ftp.slackware.com/pub/slackware/slackware-14.0/patches/packages/curl-7.60.0-i486-1_slack14.0.txz

